  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-lentil-and-avocado-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and crisp</p><p>Once the bacon is crisp, add it to a plate lined with kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and set aside, reserving the pan and any remaining oil</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-lentil-and-avocado-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your <strong>green lentils</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>avocado[s]</strong> in half lengthways, around the stone[s]</p><p>Remove the stone[s] using a spoon, then scoop out the <strong>avocado flesh </strong>and slice finely lengthways</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-lentil-and-avocado-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat and add the <strong>drained lentils </strong>along with <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> red chilli relish </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and cook for 1-2 min until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-lentil-and-avocado-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the lentils are cooking, add the <strong>remaining chilli relish</strong> to a bowl along with your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>chilli relish dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-lentil-and-avocado-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>crispy bacon</strong> to a clean board and chop roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-lentil-and-avocado-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>warmed lentils</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>salad</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>crispy bacon</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>crispy bacon & lentil salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-lentil-and-avocado-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy bacon & lentil salad</strong> with the <strong>sliced avocado </strong>over the top</p><p>Crumble over your <strong>feta </strong>and drizzle with the <strong>chilli relish dressing</strong></p><p>Top with your <strong>pumpkin seeds </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>crispy bacon</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
